Package edu.vserver.exercises.stub Description

This package contains a quick and dirty Vaadin application meant to be used as a light stub-version of ViLLE to get a more distraction free environment for developing new exercise-types for ViLLE.

The stub depends on interfaces on stable edu.vserver.exercises.model -package as does the real ViLLE. Stub however implements only the functionality directly related to exercises and does that in a quick and dirty way. The current version of stub can reliable be used only for single-user testing.

For correct behavior in real ViLLE, exercise-types developed in the stub are not allowed to rely any implementation detail of the stub (apart from the general look-and-feel). Reversions of stub with more features are likely.

Packages edu.vserver.exercises.model, edu.vserver.exercises.helpers, and edu.vserver.standardutils can be relied on. Those packages should see only new features preserving full back-wards compatibility.
